PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0
PROJECT: PrizmClaw
LANG: JavaScript (ESM), Node.js 22
DESCRIPTION: Telegram → AI CLI bridge with web admin panel; bidirectional sync, pipeline orchestration
ENTRY: src/index.js
TEST_CMD: node --test tests/**/*.test.js

MODULE_INDEX:
- src -> .prizm-docs/src/
- src/adapters -> .prizm-docs/src/adapters.prizm
- src/bot -> .prizm-docs/src/bot.prizm
- src/http -> .prizm-docs/src/http.prizm
- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/src/pipeline-infra.prizm
- src/routes -> .prizm-docs/src/routes.prizm
- src/security -> .prizm-docs/src/security.prizm
- src/services -> .prizm-docs/src/services.prizm
- src/utils -> .prizm-docs/src/utils.prizm
- public -> (static web panel assets — no L1 doc)

RULES:
- All chat messages route through messageRouter.processMessage() — never call executeAiCli directly for chat
- Session keys: bound sessions use telegram:{chatId}, unbound web sessions use web:{sessionId}
- Safe-to-modify config keys: LOG_LEVEL, REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS, AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_MS, MAX_PROMPT_CHARS, MAX_HISTORY_TURNS, SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS, SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS, TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS
- ANSI stripping happens in onAssistantChunk hook via ansiProcessChunk() — never strip in final reply path
- .btn:disabled uses pointer-events: none to prevent hover CSS from firing on disabled buttons
- .panel and .sub-panel are separate CSS rules (not grouped) to allow different box-shadow depths; shadow colors use rgba derived from --text (#1f2633) for cool-tone palette coordination
- .app-header uses position: sticky + background: var(--bg) + z-index: 10 — always pair sticky with background to prevent content bleed-through; padding-bottom + negative margin-bottom offsets border-bottom from grid gap
- .status uses modifier classes .connected (green: #ecfdf3/#a6f4c5/#027a48) and .error (red: #fef3f2/#f9d3d0/--danger) — setStatus(text, state) manages class swap; error palette reuses .message.error values for system consistency
- .message uses animation: fade-in 0.25s ease-out both — @keyframes fade-in defined in styles.css; fill-mode `both` ensures opacity:0 pre-start and opacity:1 post-end; translateY(4px)→0 adds subtle depth
- .char-counter uses classList.toggle('warning', len >= threshold) on wrapper div — warning class at 80% of CHAR_LIMIT (6400/8000); updateCharCounter() called on input event and after submit clears chatInput
- .output-box uses modifier classes .error (red: #fef3f2/#f9d3d0/--danger) and .exit-error (amber: #fffbf0/#fde8bb/--warning) — always classList.remove() both classes before each exec run to reset state; toggle .error on stderrOutput when stderr non-empty; toggle .exit-error on exitCodeOutput when exitCode !== 0
- CSS breakpoints: 900px collapses .dashboard-grid + .form-grid to 1fr; 600px mobile breakpoint adds flex-wrap on .app-header, collapses .exec-form to 1fr, reduces .panel/.sub-panel padding (14px→10px), .app-shell padding (20px→12px), .chat-messages max-height (62vh→50vh); .status gets max-width+text-overflow:ellipsis at 600px to prevent header overflow

UPDATED: 2026-03-23
